# Coding Standards

## General
- KISS — simplest solution that works
- DRY — if you write it twice, extract it
- SOLID — single responsibility, no god components
- No magic values — all constants in `src/utils/constants.js`

```js
// ❌ BAD
<section className="py-24">

// ✅ GOOD — use a consistent spacing token via CSS var
<section className="py-[var(--spacing-section)]">
```

## No Magic Strings
```js
// ❌ BAD
<a href="mailto:hello@vantagewebdesigns.com">

// ✅ GOOD
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '@/utils/constants'
<a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>
```

## File Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.jsx`
- Utilities: `camelCase.js`
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` inside the file

## PageSpeed — Hard Rule (Target: 98-100 across all Core Vitals)
This codebase has been verified at 100/100/100/100 on PageSpeed Insights (desktop). Mobile targets 95+.
- `next/image` always — never `<img>`. Always set `width`, `height`, `alt`
- Above-fold / hero images MUST have `priority` prop (eliminates LCP penalty)
- Hero image MUST use responsive `sizes` — never `sizes="100vw"` alone:
  ```jsx
  sizes="(max-width: 640px) 640px, (max-width: 1024px) 1024px, 1920px"
  ```
- Background/decorative images use `quality={60}` — heavily overlaid images don't need high quality
- Content images use `quality={75}`
- `next/font` always — never `@import` in CSS (eliminates render-blocking font requests)
- Default to Server Components — `'use client'` only when hooks/events/browser APIs are strictly needed
- No third-party scripts unless loaded via `next/script` with `strategy="lazyOnload"`
- No CSS `@import` inside component files — all styles via Tailwind or `globals.css`
- Avoid layout shift: always provide explicit dimensions for images and media
- Use native `<details>/<summary>` for accordions — zero JS, accessible, no bundle cost

## Accessibility — Hard Rule (Target: 100)
- Heading order must be sequential — never skip from h2 to h4
- `--color-muted` must maintain minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio on dark backgrounds
- Current value `#c0c0cc` on `#09090f` passes WCAG AA — do not darken it
- Never use `text-muted` on semi-transparent backgrounds (e.g. fixed header over hero image)
  Lighthouse calculates contrast against the actual rendered background including images beneath
  Use `text-text/70` instead — it's relative to the text color and always passes on dark backgrounds
- Never use opacity modifiers on muted text (e.g. `text-muted/60`) — the blended color often fails contrast
  Use full `text-muted` and rely on `line-through` or other visual cues for hierarchy instead
- Never use low opacity modifiers on white text over dark backgrounds (e.g. `text-white/20`, `text-white/30`)
  Lighthouse blends the value against the actual background color and checks the result
  On navy `#1B2434`, `text-white/55` is the minimum passing opacity (5.03:1) — never go below this

## Clickable Cards — SEO Pattern
- Wrap the entire card in `<Link>` — never put a standalone "Learn More" link inside a card
  Lighthouse's SEO audit checks visible link text, not `aria-label`
  When the card is the link, the accessible name comes from the `<h3>` heading — which is descriptive
- The visual "Learn More" affordance becomes a `<span aria-hidden="true">` inside the card link
- Hover effects use `group` on the `<Link>` and `group-hover:` on the inner span

```jsx
// ❌ BAD — Lighthouse flags "Learn More" as non-descriptive link text
<div>
  <h3>Roof Replacement</h3>
  <Link href="/services/roof-replacement">Learn More</Link>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD — accessible name is "Roof Replacement" from the h3
<Link href="/services/roof-replacement" className="group">
  <h3>Roof Replacement</h3>
  <span aria-hidden="true" className="group-hover:gap-3">Learn More →</span>
</Link>
```

## Next.js Dynamic Routes — Async Params
- In Next.js 15+, `params` is a Promise — always `await` before accessing properties
- Applies to both the page component AND `generateMetadata`

```js
// ❌ BAD
const ServicePage = ({ params }) => {
  const service = find(params.slug);

// ✅ GOOD
const ServicePage = async ({ params }) => {
  const { slug } = await params;
  const service = find(slug);
```

## Optional Features — Env Var Guard Pattern
- Any feature driven by env vars (blog, analytics, CRM) must guard at the data layer
- Return a safe empty value when the key is absent — never let it crash the build

```js
// ✅ GOOD — blog is opt-in, build passes without Notion keys
export async function getPublishedPosts() {
  if (!process.env.NOTION_API_KEY || !process.env.NOTION_DATABASE_ID) {
    return [];
  }
  // ... fetch from Notion
}
```

## Image Quality Config
- When using non-default quality values (e.g. `quality={60}`), declare them in `next.config.mjs`
  Otherwise Next.js logs a warning and may fall back to defaults

```js
// next.config.mjs
images: {
  qualities: [60, 75], // list every quality value used across the codebase
}
```

## Animations — GPU Composited Only
- Never animate `background-position`, `background-size`, `width`, `height`, `top`, `left` — these trigger paint/layout
- Only animate `transform` and `opacity` — these are GPU composited and don't cause reflow
- The `logo-shine` animation uses `transform: translateX()` on a `::after` pseudo-element — this is intentional
- Add `will-change: transform` sparingly and only when animation is known to run

## Comments
- No comments that describe what code does
- Only comment non-obvious intent or constraints

## No Em Dashes
- Never use em dashes (—) in copywriting — they look AI-generated
- Use hyphens or rephrase the sentence instead
